name: Homatus Coniflorus
description:
--Fig.10--
Homatus Coniflorus is a Palinura Hydrozoa creature from Lipperhey, an exoplanet located 40 light years from earth, orbiting the star 55 Cancri A.
Homatus lives its life flying through big fields of grass and swimming in big oceans of Argon. It lives in big swarms of billions or even trillions of individuals, resembling giant groups of flying jellyfish.
Its vivid colors and enormous flocks represent prosperity and abundance.
